result.value: LIkelihood Ratio Interpretation of Clinical AbnormaLities

LIRICAL (LIkelihood Ratio Interpretation of Clinical AbnormaLities) 
is designed to provide clinically interpretable computational analysis of phenotypic
abnormalities (encoded using the [Human Phenotype Ontology](http://www.human-phenotype-ontology.org)),
optionally combined with an analysis of variants and genotypes if a VCF file is provided with the
results of diagnostic gene panel, exome, or genome sequencing. 
and breaks down the contributions of the HPO terms and deleterious variants in the associated genes for each diagnosis: 
The report is also available in JSON/TSV formats suitable for programmatic post-processing.

Consult the documentation for *installation instructions* and a *tutorial*:
- [Stable documentation](https://thejacksonlaboratory.github.io/LIRICAL/stable)
- [Edge release documentation](https://thejacksonlaboratory.github.io/LIRICAL/latest)
Most users should download the latest distribution ZIP file from the [Releases page](https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/releases).

Consult the documentation for *installation instructions* and a *tutorial*:
- [Stable documentation](https://thejacksonlaboratory.github.io/LIRICAL/stable)
- [Edge release documentation](https://thejacksonlaboratory.github.io/LIRICAL/latest)

result.description:
A patch release with bug fixes and no novel functionality.

## What's Changed
* Remove extra `\t` from the TSV template by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/657
* Use `en_US` to run tests by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/658


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/compare/v2.0.1...v2.0.2
result.name: v2.0.2

result.description:
The `v2.0.1` includes one bug fix and no new functionality.

The bug fix rectifies the behavior of the `--sdwndv` CLI flag which is used to report the diseases with no mutations in the associated gene. Prior `v2.0.1`, the option was considered only in HTML report, and the TSV output included *all* diseases all the time. Since `v2.0.1`, the TSV report will only include a disease with no mutation found in the associated gene if the `--sdwndv` is used, and the diseases will *not* be shown by default.


## What's Changed

* Do not show the candidate disease unless there is a (predicted) pathogenic variant(s) in the associated gene by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/651
* Add docs section to describe building LIRICAL to use as a library by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/649
* Remove misplaced dependency from `lirical-configuration` POM by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/648


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/compare/v2.0.0...v2.0.1
result.name: v2.0.1

result.description:
## What's Changed

- Add `prioritize` command for running LIRICAL entirely from CLI
- Support running analysis starting from both `v1` and `v2` phenopacket versions
- Simplify the YAML input format
- Enhance HTML report, add JSON output format
- Split the codebase into several modules
- Require Java 17 or better
- Host documentation and API docs on `github.io`

## New Contributors
* @mabeckwith made their first contribution in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/595

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/compare/v1.3.4...v2.0.0

result.description:
Release candidate (2)

The last release candidate before `v2.0.0`. The `v2` will introduce many breaking changes most of which are `@Deprecated` in this release.

## What's Changed
* Rework configuration and analysis options by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/594
* Update documentation by @iimpulse in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/598 @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/602 https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/605
* Rework logging by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/603
* Implement JSON output format by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/588
* Fix Exomiser file locked error when running LIRICAL multiple times by @mabeckwith in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/595
* Shrink poisson API, improve javadoc, use selected disease databases to calculate pretest probability by @ielis in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/604

## New Contributors
* @mabeckwith made their first contribution in https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/pull/595

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/TheJacksonLaboratory/LIRICAL/compare/v2.0.0-RC1...v2.0.0-RC2
